<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Crankcase, Crankshaft, Connecting
        Rods, And Pistons - Rear Cover - Cleaning
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Cleaning</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a scraper or wire brush to remove the RTV sealant and any foreign material from the rear
                cover/oil pan mating surfaces.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a commercially available brake cleaner to clean the crankcase and rear cover gasket
                surfaces. The surfaces must be free of oil for good adhesion of RTV sealant during installation.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wipe and dry the surfaces with a clean shop cloth.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
